Reception Hosted by Ministry of Foreign Affairs 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Ministry of Foreign Affairs hosted a reception on Thursday evening on the occasion of the 47th anniversary of the victory of the Cuban revolution.
 Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun in his speech warmly congratulated the Cuban people on the day of the victory of the Cuban revolution which brought about a dramatic turn in hewing out their destiny. The victory of the Cuban revolution marked a historic event that paved the way for a worthy life of the Cuban people who were subject to poverty and the absence of rights, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fraternal Cuban people have firmly defended the gains of the revolution and victoriously advanced along the path of socialism under the leadership of Fidel Castro Ruz, while frustrating the heinous political pressure and blockade of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will as ever make positive efforts to boost the ties of friendship and cooperation with socialist Cuba in all fields and always join hands with the Cuban people in the just cause of defending socialism from imperialism in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cuban Ambassador e.p. to the DPRK Ruben Perez Valdes said in his speech that the victory of the Cuban revolution marked a historic event that gave hope to the people who were groaning under the yoke of the oppressors and paved the way for socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the Cuban people have made great successes in various fields despite the U.S. imperialists' persistent moves to isolate and stifle Cuba.
 He emphasized that the two peoples are dynamically advancing to achieve sure victory under the leadership of Supreme Commander Fidel Castro Ruz and Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il.

U.S. Hit for Raising Suspicion about "Counterfeit Notes" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity for the Implementation of the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration and Peace on the Korean Peninsula reportedly held a "press conference to denounce the U.S. for raising a groundless suspicion about counterfeit notes in the north" in the vicinity of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on Dec. 26.
 At the press conference speakers said that "counterfeit notes" racket against the north was groundless, terming this a part of dastard moves of the U.S. to hamstring the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the press conference stated that the U.S.-raised suspicion about the "counterfeit notes" is nothing but a fabrication to stifle the north. It warned that if the U.S. does not stop its hostile policy toward the north, it would face the vigorous struggle of the 70 million fellow countrymen and would be brought to a severe trial of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An open questionnaire to the U.S. government and the U.S. ambassador in Seoul was read out at the press conference.

Polish Ambassador Has Interview with Reporters 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- Polish Ambassador to the DPRK Roman Iwaszkiewicz Thursday had an interview with reporters at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on the occasion of the independence day of Poland and the New Year Juche 95 (2006).
 On hand were media persons in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the interview the ambassador referred to the Polish political situation, foreign policy and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking of the development of relations between Poland and the DPRK, he added that they would make efforts to develop friendly relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He answered the questions raised by reporters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the interview the participants went round materials introducing Poland.

Athletes of DPRK Prove Successful in 2005 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- Athletes of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have proved successful in national and international contests this year.
 Local sports contests including those for Paektusan Cup, Mangyongdae Cup and Pochonbo Torch Cup were held in the year to improve the sports technique. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Athlete of the April 25 Sports Group Kim Hyon Ung who participated in the national sports festival celebrating October 10 renewed the world record in the event of centre fire pistol. And national records of various events including weight-lifting and field and track were broken at tournaments.
 Korean sportspersons distinguished themselves at international tournaments, demonstrating the honor of Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Labor Hero and People's Sportswoman Kye Sun Hui, Kim Il Sung Prize laureate, placed the first in the 2005 World Judo Championships held in Cairo in September for the third time in succession. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean players also came first in total by bagging four trophy cups and 26 medals including 17 gold medals at the 14th World Taekwon-do Championships. They have retained the championship for the tenth in succession. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In March, June and October female pro-boxers captured and retained the championships of the IFBA and WBCF and got qualification for them.
 Korean sportspersons won nearly 100 trophies and more than 200 gold and other medals at the East Asia football championships, 23rd Universiad, 2005 Asia judo championships and 60-odd other international contests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is noticeable is that potentials were displayed for developing football and other events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The male juvenile footballers displayed their skills at the 11th world youth (under the age of 17) football championships. They took the first place at the group "N" for the 12th Asian Youth (under the age of 17) Football Championships and thus obtained the qualification for the next stage contests of the championships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Athletes snatched many gold medals in such international championships as the 7th Asian Juvenile Weightlifting Championships, 18th Youth Male Weightlifting Championships, 14th East Asian Juvenile Table-tennis Championships and other international tournaments.

KCNA Blasts Japan's Political Row over "Abduction Issue"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, December 30 (KCNA) -- The ultra-right conservative forces of Japan are persisting in their anti-DPRK despicable row over its "abduction issue".
 They held a "world meeting urging repatriation of families of those abducted to the north" in Tokyo on Dec. 22 at which they stressed the need to "intensify international solidarity" and "make joint efforts" allegedly to prevent the "tragedy" of the above-said families. In a nutshell, the "meeting" was aimed at wooing international human rights organizations and other organizations to put pressure on the DPRK over the "abduction issue".
 This is an undisguised challenge to the trend of the times as it is nothing but political rowdyism of the ultra-right conservative forces of Japan who do not know even where they should stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the DPRK-Japan inter-governmental contacts made in Beijing a few days after the meeting, both sides agreed to take measures to settle the pending issues including the issue for normalizing the bilateral relations at an early date in line with the spirit and the basic principle of the Pyongyang Declaration. 
 The conservative forces of Japan have kept staging the worn-out "abduction drama," swimming against the overall trend of the international community towards reconciliation. This is designed to divert elsewhere the world opinion following the stand and attitude of the two countries while positively assessing the moves to improve the bilateral relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When their attempt to fake up the second "abduction case" involving several countries proved futile, they busied themselves with hosting the "Osaka meeting", the "Tokyo meeting" and other meetings one after another in a bid to "put international pressure" on the DPRK.
 They are zealously toeing the U.S. line to internationally isolate and stifle the DPRK after listing it as a "terrorist state" under the pretext of the "abduction issue".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is ridiculous for Japan, a political dwarf, to curry favor with the U.S., its master, and get a sort of political reward from the latter.
 It is quite preposterous and unreasonable for Japan to seek to "internationalize the abduction issue" as it has heavy historical responsibility and moral obligation to settle its past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has not yet redeemed the hideous crimes it has perpetrated by forcibly drafting and abducting Koreans in the last century. However, it has not done away with its criminal disposition of abducting people as evidenced by the recent abduction of An Phil Hwa, a Japanese woman in the DPRK.
 The Japanese ultra-right forces are so brazen-faced as to insist only on the already settled "abduction issue" in a bid to get on the nerves of the DPRK, keeping mum about their inglorious "past." This behavior cannot be construed otherwise than a deliberate attempt to block the forthcoming inter-governmental contact. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan truly wants to make a policy switchover in the hope of warming up the bilateral relations as desired by the international community and the two peoples in the new century, it should stop the "abduction" racket at once.
